PORT HARCOURT – Embattled Governor of Edo State,  Godwin Obaseki is presently meeting with his Rivers State counterpart,  Nyesom Wike in Port Harcourt. The meeting might not be unconnected with Obaseki’s rumoured defection to the PDP to contest the September 19 governorship election. He had lost out to his estranged godfather, Comrade Adams Oshiomhole, national champion of the ruling All Progressives Congress (APC) and was consequently screened out of the Edo State governorship race on APC platform. PORT HARCOURT (Sundiata Post) - The people of Edo State have been commended for voting for Mr. Godwin Obaseki, candidate of the All Progressives Congress (APC), during Wednesday’s governorship election in the state. The Rivers State chapter of the APC made the commendation in a statement issued on Thursday afternoon,… September 29, 2016 In "News" Rivers State Governor, Nyesom Ezenwo Wike, has slammed National Chairman of All Progressives Congress (APC), Adams Oshiomhole, as a dubious and political armed robber without verifiable academic certificate. He also described Oshiomhole as a politician without character. He also described the APC National Chairman as a man always driven by… February 15, 2020 In "News" The Rivers State Chapter of the All Progressives Congress (APC) has dismissed as a pipe dream, the ambition of Minister of State, Chief Nyesome Wike, to rule the State, predicting that he will meet his political waterloo during the 2015 governorship election. “We have noted Wike’s boast that he will… August 4, 2014 In "Politics"